'''''Gemmatimonas aurantiaca''''' is a [[Gram-negative]], aerobic, [[polyphosphate]]-accumulating micro-organism.<ref name="Zhang2003">{{cite journal|last1=Zhang|first1=H.|title=Gemmatimonas aurantiaca gen. nov., sp. nov., a Gram-negative, aerobic, polyphosphate-accumulating micro-organism, the first cultured representative of the new bacterial phylum Gemmatimonadetes phyl. nov.|journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology|volume=53|issue=4|year=2003|pages=1155–1163|issn=1466-5026|doi=10.1099/ijs.0.02520-0|pmid=12892144}}</ref> It is a [[Gram-negative]], rod-shaped aerobe, with type strain T-27<sup>T</sup> (=JCM 11422<sup>T</sup> =DSM 14586<sup>T</sup>). It replicates by [[budding]].

