{{Infobox Officeholder | name = Iñaki Antigüedad | honorific-suffix = | image =Iñaki Antiguedad 2.jpg | office1 = Leader of [[Amaiur]] | term_start1 = 27 September 2011 | term_end1 = | predecessor1 = | successor1 = |office2 = Member of the [[Congress of Deputies (Spain)|Congress of Deputies]] |term_start2 = 20 November 2011 |term_end2 = |constituency2 = [[Vizcaya (Spanish Congress Electoral District)|Vizcaya]] | birth_date =1955 | birth_place =[[Bilbao]], [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque Country]] | nationality =[[Basque people|Basque]] | children = | residence = | website = | profession = [[Geologist]] }} '''Iñaki Antigüedad Auzmendi''' (born 1955, [[Bilbao]]) is a Basque geologist and politician. He is professor of [[hydrogeology]] at the [[University of the Basque Country]], and leader of [[Amaiur]].<ref name="León">{{cite news|url=http://www.publico.es/especial/elecciones-generales/2011/inaki-antiguedad.php|title=Un veterano para una marca recién creada|last=León|first=Sergio|work=Diario Público|publisher=Mediapubli Sociedad de Publicaciones y Ediciones S.L.|language=Spanish|accessdate=27 November 2011|location=Madrid|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111123094552/http://www.publico.es/especial/elecciones-generales/2011/inaki-antiguedad.php|archivedate=23 November 2011|df=}}</ref>
Following the strong performance of Amaiur in the [[2011 Spanish general election]], Antigüedad is leading a campaign to hold a [[referendum]] on [[Basque independence]].<ref name="AFP">{{cite news|url=http://www.expatica.com/es/news/spanish-news/in-basque-region-independence-fight-taken-to-ballot-box_188644.html|title=In Basque region, independence fight taken to ballot box|date=15 November 2011|work=expatica.com|publisher=[[Agence France-Presse|AFP]]|accessdate=27 November 2011}}</ref>
